Title: "Thor: Ragnarok" Official Trailer
Comment:
So the writers were talking.
Writer 1: "Hey, what would be cooler than Thor with long hair and a hammer?"
Writer 2: "Thor with short hair, and a gun."
Writer 3: "Hey, we should destroy his hammer, and shave his head. While we're at it, we can give him a power up that is way op where he can manipulate lightning and fly without his hammer thus destroying the whole point of  losing the hammer. And we can also leak it out in the trailer to get some fans hooked and other fans feel there is no point in watching the movie cause we just spoiled the ending."
Writer 1: , "Hang on, couldn't we just get Dr. Strange to fix the hammer my reversing the effects of time or whatever the hell that was?"
All the other writers at once: "Meh."
Writer 2: "OK, so what will we call it?"
Maintenance Guy who was eavesdropping: "Call it Ragnarok."
Writer 3: "Wtf is that?"
Maintenance Guy: "Oh, it's an obscure Norse term for Armageddon."
Writer 4: "Wow, I wish we knew that when we named the last Thor movie. That one threatened all nine realms, whereas this one pretty much only threatens Asgard."
Maintenance Guy: "Yeah that was kind of my fault."
Writer 2: "What do you mean?"
Maintenance Guy: "Well, you don't know this but, (takes off his cap and reveals himself to be an elderly white man with a comb-over) I am Stan Lee."
All 4 of the writers gasp in shock.
Writer 2: "You were here the whole time?"
Writer 1: "Quick, tell us who's decision it was to kill Wolverine."
Stan Lee: "Unfortunately, he has asked me to keep his identity secret for fear of his life. He does not want disgruntled fans hiring hit men. You will also not see his name in the credits because he was a ghost writer."
Writer 4: "Thanks Obama."
The End

*Disclaimer, "Thanks Obama." was the only way I could think to bring this fanfic to a close. I am not against the former president, I just thought it was funny.

Title: "Thor: Ragnarok" Official Trailer
Comment: The superhero/heroine movies have been rolled out for years now. They are becoming tired, the characters and plotline is lost in too much chaos on cramming more characters and fighting in. I loved the first Thor, Avengers, X-men movies, but the quality has declined. The bigger the budget the more they throw in fighting and SFX it loses the development of the characters. I realise it's fantasy, but I liked the story of Loki and Thor as brothers and why Loki went bad or the X-men needing to be united etc. It's all bigger budget SFX and less interest in the creation of the characters. It's become worn now with all superhero movies be it Marvel or DC. Money over some substance. This has ramped up the destruction, the "goddess of death" looks like hammy acting and merely as much fighting in as possible. Time for Thor to retire his hammer, Superman to stick to his journalism and Captain America to put down his shield etc.

Title: "Thor: Ragnarok" Official Trailer
Comment:
Damn Marvel is killing it.  DC/Warner needs to hurry up and get it together so we can have the best of both...

People are still 4getting the green Lantern flop as well. They would not listen to the creative
team and Warner Studios messed it up with their meddling. Also, IMO some big reasons they're 
messing up their DCEU... 

1. instead of doing their own thing creatively 
they're trying to follow the MCU's outline at an accelerated rate 
instead of taking their time.

2. Instead of setting up a connected DCEU with a well laid out timeline, they're all over the place 
and shoehorned their cash cow, Batman, into the lineup too soon just for
 a cash grab.

3. The DCEU is conflicting with TV versions of the characters and misappropriated villains. i.e. The Joker, Lex Luthor (DCEU) and DCTV Arrow getting all of Batman's Villains as well as Gotham's Gordon getting the other Batman villains. It's throwing everything off when they attempt to do DCEU versions of the same characters.

4.The DCEU characters and movies seem to have an identity crises. They 
are PG13 movies but want to claim they are of a darker tone. The 
characters don't seem to have settled on an ideology yet they want to 
have conflict between the characters beliefs. e.g. BvS.

5. Again with the cash grab by Warner Studios. They're not going deep into the DC
 IP to introduce some of their lesser known/less popular characters 
along side the big JL characters to help with character development and 
open up their universe. When they did try this e.g. Suicide Squad, they 
punked out by recutting the movie, ruining the continuity and 
character development..

Marvel was able to do this successfully with Ironman, Antman, Falcon, Hawkeye, Blackwidow, Dr. Strange, Black 
Panther...i could continue but now people know and love these characters
 and they can take a lead if they wanted to.

6. Studio meddling, lack of a agreed upon DCEU blueprint and a foundation for the other movies to work from.

Buy hey, those are just my opinions.

I think i got everything here... This is gonna be i guess an educational seeming ima go deep into mythology in this coment, and may be spoilers if it does come out right so read at your risk i guess question mark?

So, in Norse mythology, if my research is correct, Ragnarok was basically the age or 'Judgement' Day, where a whole bunch of gods would face off Surt/ Surtr (If you want), who was the leader of the Demon/ Fire Giant army, and originated from Muspellheim, (Mus-pell-haym: The land of Fire Giants). And his army of Demons and Fire Giants, now i believe, if not mistaken, the massive horned beast Hulk was about to smash at the end was either Surt, or some demon/ Fire Giant. Also, it was said a whole lot of gods would Die in Ragnarok, one of those including Thor... Of course he may survive but still...

Another thing i noticed is i believe that massive wolf that attacked Hulk in that one scene was Fenris or Fenrir Wolf. The Fenris/Fenrir wolf was a son of Loki and the Giantess. It took all of the Asgardians i believe and or more to bind him, and was destined to be released on Ragnarok, which is when this movie takes place.

Loki, was actually supposed to aid Surt in his raid against Asgard, but it seems hes working with Thor on this one i guess because Surt may betray him or another reason, is he is gonna betray Thor at the end. Another reason is it was said Loki were to die in Ragnarok along with Thor, so maybe thats another motive to help Thor in hopes he wont loose his life... This all prediction though...

This all prediction and thought but if you somehow hate me for this comment, please dont xD If this was already stated and i missed some interview talking about this, im late, please tell me xD

Title: "Thor: Ragnarok" Official Trailer
Comment:
This looks like it's actually going to be pretty excellent.
And I've been skeptical for multiple reasons despite a lot of good points.
One, another MCU film where they decided a character couldn't have their own movie so they put them in it (Hulk in this case, Iron Man multiple times now, etc).
The MCU films these days all get praised regardless. Civil War was good but it wasn't even a civil war it could've been better, age of ultron was a very bleh movie entirely, and this year we had GOTG2 which makes DC's Green Lantern villain look good, and then we had Spiderman: Homecoming which is full of a bunch of disney channel high school scenes and angst mixed with granted, a good Vulture and potentional set ups.
DC knocked it out of the park with Wonder Woman, but I have huge doubts Justice Leaque without more individual films (THe Flash, Cyclops, and no green lantern til 2020+) it's going to feel forced.
And also cutting out Jane Foster entirely seems kinda random, I don't get why people hated her dynamic so much. 
In any case, I expect this to be quite good, and hope Marvel keeps making Thor films and keeps the Russo brothers in charge of other projects, and maybe can get some new talent or otherwise better scripts for other things (though, Doctor Strange was great, and I wish Black Panther was out right now).
